EU , China Reach New Textile Agreement
BRUSSELS , November 21 ( Xinhua ) -- The European Union and China reached a new textile agreement Friday night after five-day arduous talks here in Brussels , officials of the Chinese Mission to the European Communities told Xinhua Saturday .
The sixth Sino-EU bilateral textile agreement was reached by the Chinese textile negotiation delegation and the European Commission delegation .
The fifth textile agreement , which has a three-year term between 1995 and 1998 , will expire on December 31 this year .
According the one-year term new agreement , the European Union raised the gross quota for 12 categories of Chinese textiles , which among others includes T-shirt , underware , shirt , skirt and socks .
